article.description: — Harlan Obioha's 15 points helped Niagara defeat Siena 66-59 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Niagara takes down Siena 66-59
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Harlan Obioha's 15 points helped Niagara defeat Siena 66-59 on Thursday night. Obioha had eight rebounds for the Purple Eagles (15-14, 11-8 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Braxton Bayless scored 14 points while finishing 7 of 8 from the floor. Ahmad Henderson II shot 2 of 9 from the field, including 0 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 7 for 7 from the line to finish with 11 points. Brendan Coyle led the Saints (4-26, 3-16) in scoring, finishing with 19 points and two steals. Giovanni Emejuru added 14 points, 10 rebounds and three steals for Siena. Michael Eley had eight points. The loss was the Saints' sixth in a row. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
